<img src="/resources/9d785522b7791c98a9ce878b65918ab2c4a7a561/CNX_Chem_09_01_Manometer5_img.jpg" data-media-type="image/jpeg" alt="A diagram of a closed-end manometer is shown. To the upper left is a spherical container labeled, &#8220;gas.&#8221; This container is connected by a valve to a U-shaped tube which is labeled &#8220;closed end&#8221; at the upper right end. The container and a portion of tube that follows are shaded pink. The lower portion of the U-shaped tube is shaded grey with the height of the gray region being greater on the right side than on the left. The difference in height of 26.4 c m is indicated with horizontal line segments and arrows."/>
</span>
</div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-idm48939344">
<p id="fs-idm83006352">(a) 264 torr; (b) 35,200 Pa; (c) 0.352 bar</p>
</div>
</div>
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-idp27847856">
