<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-idm25727664">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idm125997536">
<p id="fs-idm79130144">How would the use of a volatile liquid affect the measurement of a gas using open-ended manometers vs. closed-end manometers?</p>
</div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-idp135833360">
<p id="fs-idm51906080">With a closed-end manometer, no change would be observed, since the vaporized liquid would contribute equal, opposing pressures in both arms of the manometer tube. However, with an open-ended manometer, a higher pressure reading of the gas would be obtained than expected, since <em data-effect="italics">P</em><sub>gas</sub> = <em data-effect="italics">P</em><sub>atm</sub> + <em data-effect="italics">P</em><sub>vol liquid</sub>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<div data-type="glossary"><h3 data-type="glossary-title">Glossary</h3>
<dl id="fs-idm92046304"><dt>atmosphere (atm)</dt><dd id="fs-idm48979616">unit of pressure; 1 atm = 101,325 Pa</dd></dl>
<dl id="fs-idm49164816"><dt>bar</dt><dd id="fs-idm19523424">(bar or b) unit of pressure; 1 bar = 100,000 Pa</dd></dl>
<dl id="fs-idp128557152"><dt>barometer</dt><dd id="fs-idp44432976">device used to measure atmospheric pressure</dd></dl>
<dl id="fs-idp1898224"><dt>hydrostatic pressure</dt><dd id="fs-idm78041232">pressure exerted by a fluid due to gravity</dd></dl>
<dl id="fs-idm30126128"><dt>manometer</dt><dd id="fs-idm91258448">device used to measure the pressure of a gas trapped in a container</dd></dl>
<dl id="fs-idm69533872"><dt>pascal (Pa)</dt><dd id="fs-idm53495904">SI unit of pressure; 1 Pa = 1 N/m<sup>2</sup></dd></dl>
<dl id="fs-idm87137504"><dt>pounds per square inch (psi)</dt><dd id="fs-idm52430016">unit of pressure common in the US</dd></dl>
<dl id="fs-idm61385376"><dt>pressure</dt><dd id="fs-idm64654544">force exerted per unit area</dd></dl>
<dl id="fs-idm23965520"><dt>torr</dt><dd id="fs-idm55637456">unit of pressure; <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mtext>1 torr</mtext><mo>=</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>760</mn></mrow></mfrac><mspace width="0.2em"/><mtext>atm</mtext></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mtext>1 torr</mtext><mo>=</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>760</mn></mrow></mfrac><mspace width="0.2em"/><mtext>atm</mtext></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></dd></dl>
</div></body>

</html>